.TH "ep93xx_register_spi" 9 "ep93xx_register_spi" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ep93xx_register_spi \- registers spi platform device
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" ep93xx_register_spi
.BI "(struct ep93xx_spi_info *info "  ","
.BI "struct spi_board_info *devices "  ","
.BI "int num "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "info" 12
ep93xx board specific spi master info (__initdata)
.IP "devices" 12
SPI devices to register (__initdata)
.IP "num" 12
number of SPI devices to register
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function registers platform device for the EP93xx SPI controller and
also makes sure that SPI pins are muxed so that I2S is not using those pins.
